Rating: 0
SOUR CHERRY SAUCE 1 cup drained bottled pitted sour cherries* plus 1/2 cup of their syrup 2 tablespoons sugar 2 tablespoons dry white wine 1 teaspoon cornstarch 1 drop almond extract Pour syrup into a 1-quart heavy saucepan, setting aside cherries. Whisk sugar, wine, and cornstarch into cherry syrup until smooth, then bring to a boil over moderate heat, whisking constantly, and boil until slightly thickened, about 1 minute. Remove from heat, then stir in almond extract and cherries and cool. Cooks' note: Sauce can be made 4 days ahead and chilled, covered. *Available at specialty shops. Makes about 1 cup. Gourmet December 2005 Adapted from Café Pushkin, Moscow

